<promed@promedmail.org>
[This moderator worked with Dennis Burkitt in Uganda at the time
Dennis recognized BL as a distinct entity, & with Tony Epstein at
the time the latter discovered it was caused by the virus that bears
his name, Epstein-Barr virus (EBV, also known as human
herpesvirus 4, HHV4). I also studied the relationship of BL to
malaria in Uganda with Julian de Zulueta of WHO. We concluded
that it was coincidental, & due to some unknown geographical co-
factor common to both malaria & BL.
Among the many strange things about this tumor is that it is 100%
curable by chemotherapy (methotrexate) -- the tumour goes down
like a pricked balloon -- and that EBV has a worldwide distribution
(it's the cause of infectious mononucleosis) yet only causes
cancer in the malarious areas of Africa & Papua New Guinea,
apart from the rare cases elswhere (called the American type).
EBV is also associated with nasopharyngeal carcinoma (NPC),
which is also global in distribution but most prevalent in China.
Since malaria has been spreading to the highlands of Kenya &
PNG, perhaps somebody should be looking for BL in the New
Guinea highlands also? - Mod.JW]
